Put folowing content in a file called <ApplicationName.desktop> and put it in /usr/share/applications folder .
Then source .bashrc .

This is example to create desktop icon for Skype .

#!/usr/bin/env xdg-open
[Desktop Entry]
Version=1.0
Type=Application
Terminal=false
Exec=/snap/bin/skype
Name=Skype
Comment=Skype
Icon=/snap/skype/23/usr/share/icons/hicolor/256x256/apps/skypeforlinux.png

Just to test something
